---
/**
 * Slide 08 · Beyond Teaching — the model generalizes across sectors.
 * Teaching → health (Apprenticeship College of Health, Apr 2026) → more.
 */
const sectors = [
  { tag: "Live", k: "Teaching", d: "The proven first front — grow-your-own teachers for districts that can't recruit." },
  { tag: "New · Apr 2026", k: "Health", d: "Reach + a training fund launched an Apprenticeship College of Health, including a behavioral-health pathway." },
  { tag: "Next", k: "More sectors", d: "Any rural workforce desert with employer demand is a candidate for the same earn-and-learn engine." },
];
---

<section data-slot="08" data-variant="v1" class="deck-section">
  <span class="deck-kicker">08 / 11</span>

  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <p class="deck-eyebrow mb-3">Multi-sector expansion</p>
    <h2 class="deck-h2">The engine isn't only for teachers — <span class="deck-gradient">it's generalizing.</span></h2>
  </div>

  <div class="deck-grid mt-2 items-stretch" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));">
    {sectors.map((s) => (
      <div class="deck-card flex flex-col gap-3">
        <span class="deck-chip">{s.tag}</span>
        <p style="font-family: var(--font-heading); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--color-text); margin: 0;">{s.k}</p>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.5; margin: 0;">{s.d}</p>
      </div>
    ))}
  </div>

  <p class="deck-lede mt-2" style="max-width: 72ch;">
    Rural healthcare deserts are a natural second front. The behavioral-health pathway was
    seeded by The Goodness Web <span class="deck-verify">VERIFY</span> at roughly $1M — the
    same place-based income logic, a different workforce shortage.
  </p>
</section>
